<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> General </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Chief Expresses Regret Over Nixon's Death </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Chief Expresses Regret Over Nixon's Death </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2304223094 Beijing XINHUA in English 2056 GMT 23 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2304223094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] United Nations, April 23 (XINHUA) -- U.N. Secretary- 
General Butrus Butrus-Ghali today expressed his regret of the 
death of former U.S. President Richard Nixon, according to a 
U.N. spokesman. 
  Nixon, the 37th president of the United States, died of 
stroke on Friday [22 April], at the age of 81. 
  The spokesman said "the secretary-general had known Mr. 
Nixon 
for many years. The former President's impact in the field of 
international relations was especially significant." 
  The secretary-general has extended his condolences to the 
Nixon family, as well as to the government and the people of the 
United States, he said. 

</TEXT>

